2. Project Overview
Purpose:
Smart-Meet is a real-time video conferencing web application built using the MERN stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, Node.js) along with Agora RTC 
and RTM SDKs. The application enables users to conduct video meetings, chat in real-time, and collaborate remotely — similar to Google Meet or Zoom.
The primary goals of this project are:

To provide seamless real-time video and audio communication between multiple users
To enable in-meeting chat using Agora RTM for real-time messaging
To implement secure user authentication using JWT tokens
To support screen sharing for presentations and collaboration
To store meeting room data persistently using MongoDB Atlas

