3. Architecture
Frontend (React.js):
The frontend is built using React.js with a component-based architecture. It uses React Router DOM for client-side routing, Context API for global state 
management, and Axios for HTTP requests to the backend API.
Key frontend components:

AuthContext: Global state management for user authentication and JWT token storage
ProtectedRoute: Route guard that redirects unauthenticated users to the login page
AgoraSetup.js: Handles Agora RTC initialization, video/audio track management, and remote user handling
AgoraRTMSetup.js: Handles Agora RTM initialization for real-time in-meeting chat
Socket.js: Socket.io client configuration for real-time room events

Backend (Node.js + Express.js):
The backend follows an MVC pattern using Node.js and Express.js. It provides RESTful API endpoints for authentication and uses Socket.io for real-time 
bidirectional communication.
Key backend components:

controllers/auth.js: Handles register and login logic with bcrypt password hashing and JWT token generation
middleware/auth.js: JWT verification middleware for protecting API routes
models/User.js: Mongoose schema for user data with pre-save password hashing
models/Rooms.js: Mongoose schema for meeting room data
routes/auth.js: Express router for authentication endpoints
socket/roomHandler.js: Socket.io event handlers for room join, leave, and disconnect events

Database (MongoDB Atlas):
The application uses MongoDB Atlas as the database. Mongoose ODM is used for schema definition and database interactions.
